AI-powered sports-coaching platform (WSML 00950219). Canonical guidance: `CLAUDE.md`; PR workflow: `CONTRIBUTING.md`.

- **Current status (2026-07-02):** backend built + CI-gated (web tier, whole data layer, logging, containers, CI, CI/CD deploy pipeline — all Lior; 332 tests, `main` green). **Open lanes:** Shiri — the real model behind `POST /predict` (`ai/` is a placeholder); Elad — the live Azure deploy + demo, Forum real-time, rate-limit, stress, test-runner. Build within an open lane; don't redo the built parts. Full breakdown: `CLAUDE.md` → Current status.
- **Never push to `main`** — it's branch-protected. Branch (`feat|fix|test|docs|chore/…`) → PR → CI green (ruff · bandit · pytest) → **self-merge** (no peer approval required — own your scope + tests; CI is the gate).
- **Architecture (3 containers, only `web` exposed):** `web/` (Flask + auth/werkzeug hashing + API + frontend), `db` (MongoDB, internal), `ai/` (Random Forest + recommendation engine, internal `POST /predict`).
- **Dev switches** (full guide `docs/AUTH_TESTING.md`): **email mock ⇄ live = `SMTP_HOST`** (unset → login-OTP / signup-verify / reset codes on-screen + logged; set `SMTP_*` + `MAIL_FROM` in `.env` → emailed only; `docker compose` passes every auth-mode var through, `curl localhost:8000/auth/config` shows `email_mode`); **viewport desktop ⇄ mobile = the `?debug=1` "Debug tools" panel** (real mobile layout in an iframe on desktop; dev-only, never for normal users).
- **Constraints:** local AI model only (no external API); bake the trained model into the image (no runtime download), pin `scikit-learn`; hash passwords; validate input / guard NoSQL injection; only `web` is published; never commit `.env`; tests under `tests/{Unit,Integration,System,Stress,Security}_Tests/`.
- **No `print()`** in committed code → use `logging` (course L3/L8.1); enforced by ruff `T20` (one-off: `# noqa: T201`).
- **Hot paths → native code when measured (L6, native-vs-Python):** NumPy-vectorize first, then a Cython / C extension for a proven bottleneck; keep a pure-Python fallback, build it into the image.
- **Local gate** (mirrors CI): `sh scripts/setup-hooks.sh` + `pip install -r requirements-dev.txt` → ruff + bandit on `git commit`, pytest on `git push`.
- **TDD (course):** write tests **before/with** code; all 5 types in `tests/`. The built areas have full tests — add tests alongside new code (`tests/README.md`); the skips are **env-gated** (real Mongo / a live stack), not unwritten. Test **behaviour, not mechanism** (no `assert True`); a broken test is **fixed or deleted, never commented out**; tests run anywhere. Don't change a shared contract (`/predict`, DB collections, only-`web`-exposed) without telling the team.
